\end_inset

.
 With a single wavenumber (
\begin_inset Formula $N=1$
\end_inset

), we assume the formula is still the same, i.e.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
\begin_inset Formula 
\begin{equation}
\begin{array}{ccc}
Re & = & \frac{1}{\nu}\frac{L_{K}}{2\pi}\sqrt{\frac{1}{2}\left(\sum_{n=1}^{N}U_{n}^{2}\right)}\\
 &  & =\frac{1}{\nu}\frac{L_{K}}{2\sqrt{2}\pi}U
\end{array}\label{eq:re_WY}
\end{equation}

\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
This means 
